item.title: EQT Plans to Take Japan's Benesse Private
item.description: Swedish investment company EQT plans to take Japanese education services provider Benesse Holdings private in a deal valued at more than $1 billion, by teaming up with the company’s founding family.

item.title: Italian Government Bonds Look Chilled Ahead of Rating Review
item.description: Italian government bonds are showing no signs of downgrade anxiety, Commerzbank Research said, with Fitch due to review Italy’s “BBB” rating and stable outlook later on Friday.

item.title: Novo Nordisk Plans Expansion in Denmark
item.description: Novo Nordisk will invest over $6 billion to boost manufacturing capacity in Kalundborg, Denmark.

item.title: Richemont Sales Growth Slows as Uncertainties Persist
item.description: Richemont posted higher profits in the first half despite a slowdown in sales growth, as inflation, a weaker economy and geopolitical tensions hurt customer sentiment.

item.title: Allianz Keeps Outlook Despire Profit Drop
item.description: Allianz confirmed its operating profit target for 2023 despite reporting a lower third-quarter profit, hurt by natural-catastrophe claims.

item.title: Nikkei Edges 0.2% Lower Amid Concerns of Further Fed Tightening
item.description: Japan’s Nikkei Stock Average edged 0.2% lower to close at 32568.11 amid concerns of further Fed tightening.

item.title: Hamas Attack Victims' Family Members Call for End to War in Gaza
item.description: Three family members of victims of Hamas’s violent rampage in southern Israel on Oct. 7 spoke to The Wall Street Journal about why they are committed to promoting peace amid the war in Gaza.

item.title: China Is Making Too Much Stuff---and Other Countries Are Worried
